{"word":"πεδάω","slug":"πεδάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πεδάω</b></el> <el>(πεδάω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πέδη'><el>πέδη</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to bind with fetters, to bind fast, make fast</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to shackle, trammel, constrain</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to constrain</i> one to do a thing, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}